        "solution": "<span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Karaikal</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> is located on the </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">eastern coast of India</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, in the Union Territory of Puducherry, and lies </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">close to the Palk Strait</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, which separates India from </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">northern Sri Lanka</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">. Its proximity to Tamil Nadu’s southeastern coastline places it nearest to Sri Lanka among the given options. The Palk Strait is a </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">narrow strip of sea (approximately 40–85 km wide)</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> that connects the Bay of Bengal with the Gulf of Mannar, making Karaikal strategically significant for </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">maritime and geopolitical reasons</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span><p style=\"margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;line-height:115%;font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Important Facts:</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Karaikal</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> is an enclave within the state of </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Tamil Nadu</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, but administratively part of </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Puducherry Union Territory</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">It lies </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">south of Nagapattinam</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> and </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">north of Rameswaram</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, which is very close to </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Sri Lanka</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">The </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Palk Strait</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> and </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Adam’s Bridge (Rama’s Bridge)</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> are key physical features between India and Sri Lanka.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Mahe</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> is on the </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">west coast</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> (Kerala), while </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Yanam</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> is on the </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">east coast</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> but located in </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Andhra Pradesh</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, far from Sri Lanka.</span></li></ul>"
