        "solution": "<span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> Lakshadweep,The </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Maldives</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> is an island nation in the Indian Ocean, situated </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">to the south of Lakshadweep Islands</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, which are part of India. Both archipelagos lie in the </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Arabian Sea</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, but Maldives lies further south and west. Though </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Sri Lanka</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> also lies south of India, </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Lakshadweep is the correct Indian island group directly north of the Maldives</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span><p style=\"margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;line-height:115%;font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;color:#ff0000;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Some important facts related to the answer:</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Lakshadweep</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> is India's </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">smallest Union Territory</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, consisting of </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">36 islands</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">The </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Maldives and Lakshadweep</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> are both coral atolls.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Maldives lies </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">southwest of Kerala</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, and </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">south of Lakshadweep</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, separated by the </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Eight Degree Channel</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Both regions are ecologically sensitive and known for marine biodiversity.</span></li></ul><p style=\"margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;line-height:115%;font-size:12pt\"></p>"
