Arunachal Pradesh.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">India recognizes it as the </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">legal international boundary</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, while China calls Arunachal Pradesh “South Tibet.”</span></li></ul>"
