        "solution": "<span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> Manipur</span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">,</span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Nepal does not share its boundary with Manipur.</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> Nepal shares its international border with </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">five Indian states</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">: </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Sikkim, West Bengal, Bihar, Uttar Pradesh, and Uttarakhand</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">. </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Manipur</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, located in the </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">northeastern region of India</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, shares borders with </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Myanmar</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, not Nepal. Therefore, it does not lie near the Indo-Nepal border.</span><p style=\"margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;line-height:115%;font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;color:#ff0000;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Some important facts related to the answer:</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">The </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">India-Nepal border</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> is approximately </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">1,770 km long</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">It is an </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">open border</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, allowing visa-free movement for citizens of both countries.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Manipur</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> is part of the </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Seven Sister States</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> of northeast India.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Nepal lies to the </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">north of Bihar and Uttar Pradesh</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span></li></ul>"
