        "option_4": "<span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> Nepal</span>",
        "option_5": "",
        "answer": "3",
        "solution": "<span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> India shares the </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Sundarbans forest</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> with </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Bangladesh</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">. This </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">UNESCO World Heritage Site</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> is the </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">largest mangrove forest in the world</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, spanning the </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">southern part of West Bengal in India</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> and the </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">southwestern region of Bangladesh</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">. It lies in the </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Ganges-Brahmaputra delta</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, home to the </span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Royal Bengal Tiger</span><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> and a rich variety of flora and fauna.</span><p style=\"margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:10pt;line-height:115%;font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;color:#ff0000;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Some important facts related to the answer:</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">About 60%</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> of the Sundarbans lies in Bangladesh, the rest in India.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Known for its </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">dense mangroves</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> and </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">interconnected tidal waterways</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Plays a crucial role in </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">coastal protection and biodiversity</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Declared a </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Biosphere Reserve</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> and </span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">Ramsar Site</span><span style=\"line-height:115%;font-size:12pt;font-family:'Cambria Math'\">.</span></li></ul>"
