        "option_4": "<p><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">3</span></p>",
        "option_5": "",
        "answer": "4",
        "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">The </span><strong>Sino-Indian border</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> is divided into </span><strong>three sectors</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">: the </span><strong>Western Sector (Ladakh region)</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, the </span><strong>Middle Sector (Himachal Pradesh and Uttarakhand)</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">, and the </span><strong>Eastern Sector (Arunachal Pradesh and Sikkim)</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\">. Each sector has its own </span><strong>disputed areas</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> between India and China, with the </span><strong>Western and Eastern sectors</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'\"> being the most contentious due to differing border claims.</span></p> <p><strong>Some important facts related to the answer:</strong></p> <ul> <li><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\">The total length of the </span><strong>India-China border</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\"> is around </span><strong>3,488 km</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\"> (as per India).</span></li> <li><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\">The </span><strong>Western Sector</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\"> involves disputes around </span><strong>Aksai Chin</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\">.</span></li> <li><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\">The </span><strong>Eastern Sector</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\"> involves the </span><strong>McMahon Line</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\"> in Arunachal Pradesh.</span></li> <li><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\">Major border tensions have occurred in </span><strong>Ladakh (Galwan Valley)</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\"> and </span><strong>Tawang (Arunachal Pradesh)</strong><span style=\"font-family:'Cambria Math'; font-size:12pt\">.</span></li> </ul>"
